New role: Potato. Each night, a random role-less Villager is selected to have the ability to eat them and gain a random Villager role - however, they are not notified of this, and must have the initiative to check if there is a Potato ready to be eaten. If killed by the Maplewolf, the Potato can temporarily extend the Maplewolf's hunger by a day, given how nutritious it is. The potato cannot be revived at any point after being killed, because there isn't a Farmer role. Wolves are allergic to the Potato, and will lose their killing ability for one night after killing it.
